lines.text: [after accidentally knocking out his boss, Rawhide Buttram volunteers to help Gene Autry in Canada]
I'm not sure Canada's far enough to send you!
You gotta admit it's a step in the right direction.
[while shooting at a moose, Rawhide's rifle clicks on an empty chamber]
You can't say I didn't give a sportin' chance.
Carolina, do you see what I'm wearing to the mask-u-radee?
What is it; a bird's nest?
I put the property in Sandy's name. Just a whim, a gesture.
And to cut down on taxes.
